meta-wistron: Initial commit for meta-lannister

Add initial commit for Lannister platform.
Lannister is an x86 server platform with an ast2600 BMC.
Update OWNER list.

Tested:
1.Build Lannister image successfully.
2.The image can boot on Lannister platform.

Signed-off-by: Bob King <Bob_King@wistron.com>
Change-Id: Ibf2b8a30b56722f2fd555d356d76d199e7a9dae5

This really should be sent upstream and Joel can pick it up in our openbmc/linux distro.

OK, I will sent the dts upstream.
Thanks.
I did a fairly cursory review but high level it seems fine to me. Someone from the current OWNERS file should be able to +2 and merge.

We got the problem that the members in OWNERS file can not +2 and merge the commit.
Could you help for this?
Thanks!
Hmm, Brad do they need to be added to a team in github to get the +2?
Since this patchset is old there are a number of changes due to Yocto updates.  Would be good if these are fixed and the commit is rebased.
I'm not sure if it actually matters, but typically I see the vendor/machine layers as last.
I suspect you don't actually need meta-security unless you also want meta-security/meta-tpm, but it can be left fine.
image-prelink needs to be removed now.
This devicetree doesn't seem to exist.  How does this compile?
We already sent the patch for devicetree to kernel upstream, and it's under review.

I guess this is up to you to leave in or out, but why do you have an EFI partition on a BMC that u-boot needs to access?  It doesn't seem like you've configured eMMC, so I'm surprised you need either EFI or EXT4 in u-boot.
What does this mean?  I don't see any intel layer being used.
